Dam vandalized- water passing through in greater quantities- will be fixed in 2 weeks
Lake cloudy from wet weather- a scuba diver said there is no visibility under water.
2" of rain in the past week.
Ice 14" thick.  Ten secchi disk readings from 1.25'-11' deep.  In some spots as soon as disk went beyond ice it disappeared.  I was in 12' of water at the 11' reading.
Excellent conditions for ice fishing- ice skating- etc.  Ice 14" thick-8 different locations.  Water + slush 1-2" deep.
First reading after ice went out.  Too cold to swim.
Too cold too swim. sunny- no weeds growing at this time.
No rain- lake low- clear + sunny.
Sunny- 17 things on lake (boats- air mattresses- canoes- etc.) .
It was cloudy- sunny- overcast- etc.  4: 00 pm was about the best all day.
No snow cover- 3.25" ice.  Just a little too cold to swim.
Ice 6" thick.  It was snowing + the lake was covered with 6" of snow.
First reading after ice out.  No boats- sunny + calm.
More weeds at this time of year than in the past 8 years.
Weed cutter down for 1 week at this point.  Should have back ( ) end of this week.  Weeds to the surface.
Very heavy boat traffic Saturday 6/17/95.  Weeds very heavy.
Weeds heavy.  Cutter back at work after engine problems.  Working 6 days a week 12 hour days.
Weed cutter now fixed-cutting twelve hours a day.
This reading done about 12 hours. after very heavy rain.
Last from boat reading.  Next through the ice.  Ugh!!!
Public perception due to ice.  First reading through the ice.  Sunny- clear- cold day.  T.j.
Public perception due to ice and cold water.  Ice 13" thick. 10 degrees above- clear- sunny.
Reading after very heavy rains. surprised at seeing 11' down.
Busiest day. 17 things on lake (cones- sailboats- floats- etc.)
Milfoil at peak. 16-20 tons a day cut.
Sunny- 8 jet skis- first time this many.
Water is blue green.  First reading after ice out.
Water is greenish brown.  Full sun.
Water is greenish brown.  Full sun.
Water is greenish brown. heavy rains last night.
Water is bluish green.  Have been on vacation out of state.
First two readings for secchi line went much easier- thanks
Whole lake treatment for sonar (for Eurasion Watermilfoil) first lake in the state- on 9/30-97.
